txt.en: You have turned in a stack of trophies for a modest reward suitable for a collector such as yourself.
Wanted: Toughened carapaces from the insects and spiders surrounding Aughaire. Deliver the items to Raith at Aughaire in the south-western reaches of Angmar.
'These will be used for crafting much for our people. Thank you.'
'We can use the carapaces from the insects and spiders to ornament and reinforce our armour and clothing.'
Council of the North Task: Toughened Carapaces
The Hillmen at Aughaire have requested a collection of toughened carapaces to be delivered to Raith.
Deliver the toughened carapaces to Raith at Aughaire in Angmar
You have accepted a task to collect and deliver toughened carapaces from the insects and spiders surrounding Aughaire to Raith, a Hillman within the settlement.
Wanted: Toughened carapaces from the insects and spiders surrounding Aughaire.
